{"article_id":"AT8q8v6GoD6c6aOo","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Get all the latest news on coronavirus and more delivered daily to your inbox .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Sign up here .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"If you ' re following the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention ' s","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"( CDC 's )","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"recently updated guidelines on face masks amid the coronavirus epidemic in the U.S. ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"you likely already know to wear either a homemade mask , bandanna or some other cloth face covering","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"when running essential errands ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"namely as a way","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"to protect others from developing a COVID-19 infection .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"But equally as important","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"as wearing a face covering","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"is cleaning it properly","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"after you ' re back home .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"To make sure","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"you ' re following protocol","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"as recommended by infectious disease and other medical specialists across the nation ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"read on for a look at some of the tips below .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"The first and most obvious method","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"of cleaning a facial covering","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"is by throwing it in a washing machine .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"\" A washing machine should suffice","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"in properly washing a face covering , \"","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"says the CDC ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"noting","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"the mask should be \" routinely washed","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"depending on the frequency of use . \"","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Viruses on clothes and fabrics are typically inactivated","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"when washed in water at 140 degrees Fahrenheit ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"as per the World Health Organization 's","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"( WHO 's )","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"guidelines .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"But most at-home water heaters only reach 120 degrees Fahrenheit .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"This means it is extra important to use detergent , as well as chlorine or color-safe bleach","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"to help decontaminate the fabric as best as possible ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"according to Popular Science .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Then ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"after washing ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"make sure to dry to mask at high heat in the dryer .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Placing the face mask in boiling water is also an option ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"namely if a washing machine is not available .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"\" Use a large pot and enough water","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"to make sure","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"it doesn ' t all evaporate away .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Leave the mask in the water for several minutes","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"and swirl it around occasionally with tongs , \"","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"explained Digital Trends .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Ironing the face mask at high heat can also be helpful","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"when attempting to disinfect it ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Dimitar Marinov , an assistant professor in the department of hygiene at the Medical University of Varna , told the Huffington Post .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"MAKING A CORONAVIRUS FACE MASK :","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"DERMATOLOGIST OFFERS ADVICE ON BEST MATERIALS ,","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"HOW TO SOOTHE IRRITATED SKIN","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"Hand washing the mask is also a possibility .","depth":4},{"id":53,"text":"Lather the fabric with hot water and soap","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"and scrub it vigorously for at least 20 seconds ,","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"and use hot air","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":